# Project GENESIS v2 - Activation Plan

## Goal
To initialize the "GENESIS" autonomous business ecosystem and launch the first profit-generating pilot project. This plan outlines the construction of the central management dashboard ("Genesis Core") and proposes candidate Micro-SaaS ventures for the first "Explorer" cycle.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> **Decision Made**: **Option A: "Readme-AI"** has been selected as the pilot venture.

## Proposed Architecture: "Genesis Core" (Primary MVP)
We will build the central command center to manage the entire portfolio of experiments.
- **Frontend**: Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + Shadcn UI
- **Backend**: Next.js API Routes (Serverless)
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL) - Storing Projects, Ideas, and Logs.
- **AI Engine**: **Google Gemini 1.5 Pro / Flash** (Central Brain)
- **Analytics**: **Google Analytics 4 (GA4)** + **BigQuery** (Data Warehouse)
    - *Reason*: To leverage the Google ecosystem and enable deep analysis with Gemini.
- **Features**:
    - **Dashboard**: High-level metrics (Active Projects, Total Revenue, Success Rate).
    - **Project Manager**: Create, Edit, Archive projects (e.g., Readme-AI).
    - **Idea Bank**: Store and rank new business ideas.
    - **Experiment Logs**: Track daily progress and outcomes of each project.

## Phase 1: Infrastructure Setup
We will establish the "Factory" that produces businesses.
- [ ] Initialize Next.js project with TypeScript & Tailwind.
- [ ] Setup Supabase project (Auth + DB).
- [ ] Implement "Genesis Dashboard" (UI to view project status, metrics, and logs).
- [ ] Create "Explorer Agent" skeleton (Python scripts for trend analysis).

## Phase 2: Pilot Venture Options (Select One)
To test the "Small Start & Fail Fast" principle, we need a pilot project.

### Option A: **"Readme-AI" (Developer Tool)**
- **Concept**: A CLI/Web tool that reads a codebase and generates a perfect `README.md` using LLMs.
- **Target**: Developers, Open Source contributors.
- **Monetization**: Freemium (Basic free, Pro templates/hosting paid).
- **Why**: High demand, clear "Pain Point", easy to market on Twitter/Reddit. Uses **Gemini API** for content generation.

### Option B: **"PrivacyScrub" (Image Utility)**
- **Concept**: A drag-and-drop tool to remove EXIF/Metadata from images before sharing online.
- **Target**: Privacy-conscious users, photographers.
- **Monetization**: Free (Ad-supported) or Bulk processing (Paid).
- **Why**: Simple logic, privacy is a trending topic, low maintenance.

### Option C: **"TrendDigest" (Niche Newsletter)**
- **Concept**: Automated newsletter that aggregates "AI Tools for X" (e.g., Designers, Writers) daily.
- **Target**: Professionals trying to keep up with AI.
- **Monetization**: Affiliate links, Sponsorships.
- **Why**: "Digital Content" category, fully automatable content pipeline.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- **Unit Tests**: Jest/Vitest for utility functions (e.g., data parsers).
- **E2E Tests**: Playwright to verify the Dashboard loads and Auth works.

### Manual Verification
- **Deployment**: Verify Vercel deployment is successful.
- **Supabase Connection**: Verify data can be read/written to the DB.
- **Pilot MVP**: Verify the core function of the selected pilot works (e.g., generates a Readme, cleans an image).
